events.name: Detroit Lions at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: — David Montgomery never beat the Green Bay Packers during his four seasons with the Chicago Bears.
headlines.shortLinkText: David Montgomery runs wild as Lions beat Packers 34-20 to take early command of NFC North

headlines.description: — Calvin Ridley is making the most of his second chance, in more ways than one.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lawrence, Ridley and defense help Jaguars beat Falcons 23-7 in London

headlines.description: — Stefon Diggs was so elusive on Sunday, the Bills' star receiver even came away with two full cups of beer while celebrating the second of his three touchdown catches.
headlines.shortLinkText: Josh Allen throws 4 TD passes, runs for score, Bills rout division rival Dolphins 48-20

headlines.description: — The Denver Broncos came in reeling from a 50-point blowout and looked like they were headed toward another lopsided loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell Wilson throws 3 TDs, Broncos rally from 21 down to top Bears 31-28

headlines.description: — Baltimore was missing two receivers and its starting left tackle, later joined on the sideline by the starting right tackle. Its thin secondary was further depleted when two more defensive backs got hurt.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamar Jackson has 4 TDs as Ravens roll to 28-3 win over Browns and rookie QB Thompson-Robinson

headlines.description: — The Tennessee Titans now know what they’re capable of when they're not making mistakes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Henry runs for TD, throws for score as Titans rout Burrow, Bengals 27-3

events.name: Los Angeles Rams at Indianapolis Colts

headlines.description: — Matthew Stafford stumbled, slipped and limped his way through the final 20 minutes of regulation Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stafford overcomes injury to throw winning TD pass to Nacua in OT to give Rams 29-23 win over Colts

events.name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: — Baker Mayfield might have landed with the right team at the right time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baker Mayfield has 3 TD passes, ailing Derek Carr ineffective as Buccaneers top Saints 26-9

headlines.description: — A.J. Brown saw more than a spark out of Jalen Hurts.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hurts throws for 319 yards, Elliott's 54-yarder lifts 4-0 Eagles past Commanders 34-31 in OT

headlines.description: — Minnesota Vikings safety Harrison Smith said he didn't come into Sunday's game expecting to be an integral part of the team's defensive pressure package.
headlines.shortLinkText: Justin Jefferson's 2 TDs, D.J. Wonnum's 51-yard fumble return lift Vikings over Panthers 21-13

headlines.description: — C.J. Stroud has thrown for the second-most yards by a rookie through his first four games in NFL history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stroud throws for 306 yards, two TDs to lead Texans over Steelers 30-6; Pickett leaves with injury

events.name: Las Vegas Raiders at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: — With their $252.5 million quarterback wearing a splint on his non-throwing hand and down three starters on defense, the Los Angeles Chargers found a way to gut out their second straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Khalil Mack's 6 sacks, Justin Herbert's 3 touchdowns propel Chargers to 24-17 win over Raiders

events.name: New England Patriots at Dallas Cowboys

headlines.description: — Dak Prescott is getting used to sitting back and watching the Dallas defense do its thing.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cowboys score twice on defense in 38-3 blowout of Patriots, Belichick's worst loss

headlines.description: — The only person who could stop Christian McCaffrey from tying a San Francisco franchise record with a fifth touchdown was his own coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCaffrey scores 4 TDs to lead the 49ers past the Cardinals 35-16

events.name: Kansas City Chiefs at New York Jets

headlines.description: — Patrick Mahomes and the Kansas City Chiefs appeared on their way to a blowout against the struggling New York Jets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Patrick Mahomes, Chiefs hold on to beat Jets 23-20 with Taylor Swift, Aaron Rodgers watching

events.name: Seattle Seahawks at New York Giants

headlines.description: — With all the points the Seattle Seahawks were scoring this season, it was easy to overlook their defense.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rookie Devon Witherspoon scores on 97-yard pick-6 as Seahawks' defense leads Seattle over Giants
